Packers Re-Sign Linebacker Hawk a Day After His Release, NFL Network Says

-- B y   J a y   B e b e r m a n
-- 
2011-03-03T18:15:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/packers-re-sign-linebacker-hawk-a-day-after-his-release-nfl-network-says.html
The Super Bowl champion Green 
Bay Packers re-signed A.J.Hawk one day after he was released 
for financial reasons, the NFL Network reported, citing the 
linebacker’s agent.  Hawk, 27, was scheduled to make $10.5 million next season.  Terms weren’t disclosed, the NFL Network said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  